---
source: crates/pensum/tests/contract.rs
assertion_line: 445
expression: out
---
pen acm x -c
  # a determined series is minted by its determinant
  => exit 2: pensum's register is nameless and minted by the node's first task, so -c mints nothing (§7.1, §7.3)
pen acm x -a 260719
  # a task keys by its name, not a date
  => exit 2: a task keys by its name, not by a date, so -a keys nothing — a deadline is a Fasti event referencing the task (§5.4, §8.4)
pen series acm weight
  # pensum's register is nameless
  => exit 2: `pen series` takes one node and nothing else: pensum's register is nameless, so there is no collection to name (§7.1, §7.3)
pen list -k log
  # a token this core does not own
  => exit 2: pensum has no "log" token; it declares `task` (§7.1)
pen get never_written
  # no task by that key
  => exit 4: no pensum record keyed never_written (§7.3)
pen series ac
  # no register at that node yet
  => exit 4: no pensum register at ac — a node's first task mints one (§7.3, §8.5)
pen get buy_milk
  # one key at two nodes is listed, not guessed
  => exit 2: buy_milk keys a record at more than one node: acm, ao — name one with -H (§7.3)
pen get
  # naming nothing
  => exit 2: name the pensum record (§7.3)
pen rm -H acm buy_milk
  # a mutation piped without -y
  => exit 5: (a rm plan awaiting -y, not an error)
